      "text": "No OneDrive. The Pictures folder only has Screenshots and Smart Game Booster subfolders. The Gemini chat JSON has many `driveImage` references — these are images uploaded to the AI Studio (likely the user's photos of the inventory pages).\n\nSo the original inventory photos would be:\n- Photos Richard took of the inventory pages\n- Uploaded to Gemini on 29/03/2026\n- Referenced as `driveImage` entries with Google Drive IDs like `1eEWpuUtBf4d2tWgEccn6SzwH3g6in6R1`\n\nThese images are stored on Google's servers, not on the local disk. But the user might also have local copies of them. Let me look for them with the modified date filter and broader file extensions search.\n\nActually, since the user said they \"photocopied\" the original report, maybe the photos are scattered somewhere. Let me search:\n1. Camera Roll-style folders \n2. JPEG/PNG files modified around late March 2026\n3. The Recycle Bin\n\nWait — looking back at the user's prompt: \"the original report that was sent to richard and that then i like photocopied or sth\"\n\n\"photocopied\" suggests a paper copy. The user might mean the original Bairstow Eves PDF that was emailed to him (the actual landlord-issued inventory), which he then printed or scanned. So there should be a clean PDF from Bairstow Eves somewhere.\n\nLet me search for ALL PDFs in Documents, Downloads, and look at ones I might have missed. Also search for files with the date when Bairstow Eves would have sent it (likely 27-29 March 2026 or earlier).\n\nActually — wait. Looking at the four files I have:\n- 30/03/2026 01:25 - 17 Gedling Street.pdf (1.04 MB) \n- 30/03/2026 01:56 - 17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf (1.13 MB)\n- 30/03/2026 02:32 - 17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf (1.24 MB)\n- 30/03/2026 19:41 - 17 Gedling Street.docx (9.2 MB)\n\nWhen I read the 01:25 file just now, I see content like:\n- \"Radiators to be tested, as not clearly marked as tested anywhere\"\n- \"I have received the