      "text": "Now I understand. The PDF I read (`17 Gedling Street.pdf`) is clearly an AMENDMENTS document — Richard's voice disputing the inventory. It cites \"I have received the Gas Safety Record,\" \"I require confirmation,\" \"Marked as 'Good' is an opinion,\" etc. This is the tenant's amendment, not the original Bairstow Eves inventory.\n\nSo the original Bairstow Eves inventory check-in report — the landlord-issued document that was sent to Richard — must be somewhere else. The user photocopied/scanned it.\n\nLet me check the Downloads folders more carefully. I see `ilovepdf_extracted-pages (1)` which is interesting — that name suggests PDFs were extracted/merged. There are also `archive (1)`, `archive`, etc.\n\nAlso `AFJ Cardiff - Secure Document Vault` — that might be related but probably not.\n\nLet me search for files modified around 27-30 March 2026 (when the inventory would have been issued), particularly PDFs or images in Downloads. The user moved in around then, got the inventory, and would have scanned it.\n\nActually, looking at the file `17 Gedling Street.pdf` (30/03/2026 01:25) — that's 1.04 MB and 10 pages. The amendments on pages 5, 6, 7 show:\n- Page 5: A photo with reference codes R5.FL1.ii and R5.FL1.iii — these look like they came from the ORIGINAL inventory (a scanned page of the inventory document showing floors with photos)\n- Page 6: A photo showing \"Holes from previous fixtures: 6\" and \"No Stains / Freshly painted\" — this is from the ORIGINAL inventory\n- Page 7: A photo showing \"Alarms / Unable to verify / Dining room / Alarm not set\" — from the ORIGINAL inventory\n- Page 8: A photo of \"Lean too / Clean condition / Fitted units / Wood next to door a little rotten\" — from the ORIGINAL inventory, with red circle around the rotten wood note\n- Page 10: A photo showing \"Living Room - Fixtures & Fittings / R6.FI1 / Radiator valve caps missing\" — from the ORIGINAL inventory\n\nSo Richard embedded PHOTOS of the original inventory pages into his amendments PDF. The user photocopied (took photos of) the original inventory pages and embedded them as evidence in his amendments.\n\nSo the ORIGINAL inventory PDF must be the landlord's document. Where is it?\n\nLet me search more broadly:\n- The `ilovepdf_extracted-pages (1)` folder is suspicious — iLovePDF is a PDF manipulation tool\n- Maybe the original inventory is in there\n- Or maybe in a hidden folder somewhere\n\nLet me check that folder and also check for any PDFs modified on 27-29 March 2026.\n\nAlso let me look at the WhatsApp Chat folders — maybe there's a relevant chat.\n\nLet me focus on finding the original Bairstow Eves inventory. It would be:\n- A PDF file\n- Modified around 27-29 March 2026 (when Richard moved in)\n- OR could be the photo files themselves that Richard took of the paper inventory\n\nLooking at the modifications, the early March 2026 dates are when Richard would have received the inventory. Let me search specifically for files dated between 25 March and 30 March 2026 that might be the inventory.\n\nActually, let me also check the email files. Maybe the original Bairstow Eves inventory PDF is in the email archives.\n\nAlso looking at file dates:\n- 30/03/2026 01:25 = `17 Gedling Street.pdf` (Richard's first draft amendments)\n- 30/03/2026 01:56 = `17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf` (Richard's second draft)\n- 30/03/2026 02:32 = `17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf` (Richard's final amendments)\n- 30/03/2026 02:56 = email to richardboat52@gmail.com\n- 30/06/2026 20:26 = check-out report\n- 30/06/2026 20:44 = StefaniaOkereke folder re-share\n\nWait — the email at 02:56 is FROM andiekobbietks@outlook.com TO richardboat52@gmail.com. The user said \"the original report that was sent to Richard\" — maybe Richard IS richardboat52@gmail.com, and the email PDF shows what Richard sent to himself or what the original looked like.\n\nActually, looking at it differently: the Yahoo Mail PDF is the email