s of the inventory and shower to Gemini. Those photos were uploaded to Google's servers, not stored locally on this machine. But the EXTRACTED Google AI Studio folder DOES contain images! Look at the listing — there are `camera(3).jpg` through `camera(24).jpg` and `IMG_6048.png` etc. Those might be the photos.\n\nLet me check if any of the camera or IMG files are photos of the inventory pages. The dates 25/06/2026 are when the files were extracted from AI Studio, not when the photos were taken.\n\nLet me read the AI Studio JSON file to see what images were uploaded in the \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory\" chat.\n\nActually, looking at the most recent output, I see the truncated listing includes many files. Let me get the FULL listing without truncation, or check specific files.\n\nLet me look at:\n1. The camera(N).jpg files - some of these might be inventory photos\n2. The IMG_*.png files\n3. Read the late March Paste files to understand context\n\nThe most direct approach: read the AI Studio chat JSON file (the \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory\" one) which I read earlier. That JSON references images by ID. The IDs correspond to files in the AI Studio extracted folder.\n\nActually I already read this file. Let me re-examine what I got.\n\nEarlier in this session, I read the \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory_\" file. Let me see — what was in that file? Looking back, I noted it was a JSON AI Studio session export but didn't see the content. Let me re-read it and look at the image references.\n\nActually wait — the user might literally have photocopied the Bairstow Eves report — meaning scanned pages. The scans might be saved as JPG/PNG files somewhere. Let me search for images modified around late March 2026 specifically.\n\nLet me also check the \"Scan\" folder locations on Windows. Common ones:\n- C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\Scans\n- C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Pictures\\Scans\n- C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\OneDrive\\Documents\\Scans\n\nI already checked Documents — no Scans folder. Let me also look more broadly.\n\nHmm — looking at the user message again: \"the orignal report that was sent to richard\". The user is talking about Richard (the tenant). They say \"i am looking for\" — meaning they, the user, are looking for it. They're asking ME to find it.\n\nGiven all my searches, the only files related to 17 Gedling Street are:\n1. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\17 Gedling Street.pdf (Richard's first draft amendment)\n2. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf (Richard's second draft)\n3. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf (Richard's final amendments)\n4. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\17 Gedling Street.docx (consolidated)\n5. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\StefaniaOkereke\\17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf (duplicate)\n6. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\StefaniaOkereke\\17 Gedling Street- check out_260630_202424.pdf\n7. C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\StefaniaOkereke\\Yahoo Mail - URGENT_ Inventory Discrepancies and Reported Safety Hazards - 17 Gedling Street.pdf\n8. AI Studio extracted: 17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf\n9. AI Studio extracted: Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory_ (JSON)\n\nThe ORIGINAL Bairstow Eves inventory PDF doesn't appear to be on this machine. But the photocopies Richard took (embedded in his amendments as cropped photos) ARE there — those are in `17 Gedling Street.pdf`, `17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf`, etc.\n\nWAIT. Let me re-read the user's request: \"the orignal report that was sent to richard and that then i like photocopied or sth\"\n\nWhat if \"the original report\" IS one of the files I already found? What if Richard photocopied it by making a PDF copy/scan, and the user (who is different from Richard?) is looking for that copy?\n\nThe user's name might be Andrea Enning (based on the various files seen - \"Andrea Enning Updated CV\", etc.), and Richard is her tenant/husband/partner? Or they could be the same person with multiple identities?\n\nLooking at the email PDF content (which I read earlier), it was sent FROM `andiekobbietks@outlook.com` TO `richardboat52@gmail.com`. So Andrea sent it TO Richard. They are different people.\n\nWait — but the email is signed \"Kind regards, Richard\". So maybe \"Richard\" is signing as if he was sending the email. Or maybe Richard is the landlord's contact and Andrea is forwarding to him.\n\nActually re-reading: \"I am writing to formally report...\" signed \"Richard\". So the email was sent FROM Andrea's account but on behalf of Richard, or Richard wrote it and Andrea sent it.\n\nHmm, this is getting complex. Let me just present what I've found to the user and ask for more clarification if needed.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the email PDF content I read earlier:\n- From: andiekobbietks@outlook.com\n- To: richardboat52@gmail.com  \n- Subject: URGENT: Inventory Discrepancies and Reported Safety Hazards - 17 Gedling Street\n- Date: Mon, 30 Mar 02:56:22 +0000 2026\n- Signed: \"Kind regards, Richard\"\n\nThis email is FROM Andrea's account TO Richard's account, signed by Richard. So the user is sending the email FROM their account (Andrea's) TO themselves via Richard's account, and signing as Richard. Or maybe the user IS Richard and has two accounts.\n\nLooking at the Yahoo Mail PDF more carefully (I should re-read it), this email is a DRAFT or FORWARDED email. The user might be the actual recipient \"Richard\" who saved it to their Yahoo account. Then they put a copy in the StefaniaOkereke folder on 30/06/2026.\n\nHmm, actually it makes more sense that Andrea is forwarding Richard's email to herself or saving it. Let me re-read the email PDF.\n\nAnyway, let me focus. The user wants me to find the original Bairstow Eves inventory that Richard photocopied. Looking at the existing files, the closest match would be `17 Gedling Street.pdf` — but I've confirmed that contains Richard's AMENDMENTS, not the original inventory.\n\nCould there be a Bairstow Eves inventory in the AI Studio extracted data? Let me search through all files in those extracted folders for any inventory-like PDF. Looking at the truncated listing, I see many files but none specifically named \"Inventory\" or \"Bairstow\".\n\nWait — looking at the listing again, there's a file called \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory_\" with no extension. This is a JSON AI Studio session. But the user mentioned in their AI Studio chat that they have \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory\" — meaning this AI Studio session was about analyzing the shower rail which had a discrepancy vs what the inventory claimed.\n\nIn that AI Studio session, the user uploaded photos of the shower. Those photos would be in the AI Studio extracted folder. Looking at the camera photos:\n- camera(3).jpg through camera(24).jpg (22 files total, some gaps)\n\nThese could be the photos Richard took with his phone camera of various things, including the inventory pages and the shower.\n\nLet me read a few of these camera photos to see if they're inventory scans. I should also check the IMG_6048-6051.png files.\n\nActually, I realize I should re-read the AI Studio JSON to see what images were referenced in the conversation. The image references like \"1eEWpuUtBf4d2tWgEccn6SzwH3g6in6R1\" are Google Drive file IDs. The actual files in the extracted folder might be the actual photos uploaded.\n\nLet me also check the larger extracted folders (003 and 005) for any inventory content.\n\nActually let me also check: maybe the \"17 Gedling Street.pdf\" actually IS the original Bairstow Eves inventory, not Richard's amendments. Let me re-read it carefully.\n\nI just read it - and confirmed it's RICHARD'S AMENDMENTS:\n- \"I have received the Gas Safety Record, which confirms...\"\n- \"Marked as 'Good' is an opinion; 'Tested' is a fact:\"\n- \"I require confirmation that the heating system...\"\n- \"Formally requ