 of Richard's amendments. But it's NOT the original Bairstow Eves inventory.\n\nWhat if the original Bairstow Eves inventory is actually the FIRST file Richard worked on, and the amendments are LATER versions? Let me think...\n\nLooking at the four amendments files:\n- 30/03/2026 01:25 = `17 Gedling Street.pdf` (Richard's 1st draft - actually a draft amendment)\n- 30/03/2026 01:56 = `17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf` (2nd version)\n- 30/03/2026 02:32 = `17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf` (3rd version - final)\n- 30/03/2026 19:41 = `17 Gedling Street.docx` (consolidated)\n\nALL of these are Richard's amendments. None of them is the original Bairstow Eves inventory.\n\nOK, I think the original Bairstow Eves inventory PDF is genuinely not on this machine. The user might have:\n1. Lost it\n2. Stored it on another device\n3. Deleted it\n4. The original was never saved as a PDF on this machine\n\nWait — let me look at one more thing. The \"17 Gedling Street.pdf\" I read shows references to \"Section 11 of the Landlord and Tenant Act 1985\" and discusses the inventory items. So this is Richard's analysis of the inventory, not the inventory itself.\n\nThe original Bairstow Eves inventory would be a separate document, likely with:\n- Bairstow Eves letterhead\n- A more formal tone (third person, professional inventory clerk)\n- Just the condition notes, no commentary\n\nLet me check the WhatsApp Chat folders — those might have inventory PDFs shared.\n\nAlso, let me check if there are any PDFs dated before 30/03/2026 in the Downloads folder (before the amendments werewritten).",
