ps missing\" circled in red).\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the photos embedded in `17 Gedling Street.pdf` (30/03/2026 01:25). When I read this PDF, I saw photos of the photocopied inventory pages. Those photos ARE the photocopies.\n\nBut the user said \"i am looking for the orignal report that was sent to richard and that then i like photocopied or sth\". The \"or sth\" might mean they're uncertain whether they photocopied or scanned or photographed. The photocopies are the photos embedded in the amendments.\n\nOR... maybe the user wants me to look at the original Bairstow Eves PDF (the landlord's document), not the photocopies. In which case it genuinely isn't on this machine.\n\nI should be honest with the user. Let me just respond honestly that the original Bairstow Eves inventory is not on this machine, and the closest thing to the \"photocopies\" Richard made are the photos embedded in the amendments PDFs (which I can extract and show them).\n\nActually, let me look at the photos that are embedded in the various amendment PDFs. Those would be the photocopies Richard made. I extracted them from the .docx already — image13.png is a clear photocopy of the inventory page.\n\nLet me also check what images are in the other PDFs (the smaller PDFs). They might have copies of the photocopies that are cleaner.\n\nActually, looking back at my analysis of `17 Gedling Street.pdf`:\n- Page 5 shows a photo of the inventory table with photos labeled R5.FL1.ii, R5.FL1.iii (cropped photocopy)\n- Page 6 shows a photo with \"Holes from previous fixtures: 6\" (cropped photocopy)\n- Page 7 shows a photo with \"Alarms / Unable to verify\" (cropped photocopy)\n- Page 8 shows a photo with \"Lean too / Wood next to door a little rotten\" with red circle (cropped photocopy)\n- Page 10 shows a photo with \"Living Room - Fixtures & Fittings\" table (cropped photocopy)\n\nThese are the photocopies. They're cropped/zoomed sections of the original Bairstow Eves inventory pages.\n\nSo the user is asking for the ORIGINAL, which is not on this machine. The PHOTOCOPIES (as cropped photos) are in the PDFs.\n\nI think I need to be direct: the original isn't here, but the photocopies (as photos embedded in the amendments PDFs) are here. Let me give them a clear answer.\n\nWait, let me also check the AI Studio chat JSON content one more time. The chat was from 29/03/2026 about \"Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory\". The user uploaded photos of the inventory and shower to Gemini. Those photos would be in the Gemini chat as driveImage references.\n\nLet me look at the chat JSON again to see what was discussed and what images were uploaded. The content I read earlier showed it was about the shower. There might have been an inventory-related chat elsewhere.\n\nActually, I see in the AI Studio 001 listing there's `Discrepancy in Shower Rail Inventory_` (29/03/2026 19:00, 4452906 bytes). This is the chat JSON. The chat is about the shower discrepancy. The user uploaded photos of the shower rail.\n\nSo the Gemini chat might NOT contain the inventory scans. The inventory scans might just be in the amendments PDFs as cropped photos.\n\nOK let me just be honest with the user now. I've searched exhaustively. The original Bairstow Eves inventory is NOT on this machine. The photocopies are embedded as cropped photos in the amendment PDFs (which I can show them).\n\nI should also offer to extract the photos and show them what Richard's photocopies look like, since that's the closest thing to the original I can find.\n\nLet me also consider: maybe the user is asking me to look at the .docx file (which I haven't fully read yet). The .docx is 9.6MB and has 16 embedded images — some of which I've already extracted and viewed. image13.png was a clear photocopy.\n\nMaybe the .docx contains the FULL original Bairstow Eves inventory embedded as images (the photocopies Richard made)? Let me extract and view all 16 images from the .docx.\n\nActually, the extracted images from the .docx include image6.png which showed \"Holes from previous fixtures: 6\" — that's a clear photocopy of an inventory page. And image10.png which showed \"Lean too / Wood next to door a little rotten\" — another clear photocopy.\n\nSo the .docx has photocopies of the original Bairstow Eves inventory pages. The user might be looking for THESE.\n\nBut I've already extracted them to `gedling_extract/`. Let me list them all and send the key ones to the user.\n\nActually, I realize I should also check if the .docx contains a complete embedded image of the original Bairstow Eves inventory (as a single image). That would be the easiest answer.\n\nLet me check the sizes of the images more carefully:\n- image1.png: 849KB (could be full page scan)\n- image2.png: 840KB (could be full page scan)\n- image6.png: 1094KB (could be full page scan)\n- image10.png: 888KB (could be full page scan)\n- image12.png: 1913KB (definitely a full page scan or photo)\n- image13.png: 1462KB (definitely a full page scan or photo)\n\nimage12 and image13 are big. image13 is the \"Living Room - Fixtures & Fittings\" photocopy I already showed. Let me also check image12 — it was Google Street View (not a photocopy).\n\nLet me check the other images I haven't viewed yet (image3-11, image14-16) to see if any are full-page inventory scans.\n\nActually, given the user is repeating the question for the third time, I should just be direct now and tell them what I've found:\n\n1. The original Bairstow Eves inventory PDF is NOT on this machine\n2. The photocopies Richard made are embedded in `17 Gedling Street.pdf`, `17 Gedling Street (Finale Report Amendments).pdf`, `17 Gedling Street - Ultimate Amendments Sheets.pdf`, and `17 Gedling Street.docx`\n3. I extracted the 16 images from the .docx to `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.mavis\\sessions\\mvs_e93797d3d3764154b3f3ca0d3c8dc9af\\workspace\\gedling_extract\\`\n4. Some of those images (image6, image10, image13) are clear photocopies of Bairstow Eves inventory pages